In the INTEREST OF: C.J.L., S.L.L., L.D.L. Juvenile Officer, Respondent,
v.
S.L. (Father), Appellant. WD 81692 Consolidated with WD 81694
WD 81696 Missouri Court of Appeals, Western District. Filed: November 6, 2018 Jack A. Lewis, North Kansas City for appellant. John R. Shank, Joseph W. Vanover for respondent Juvenile Officer; Juliann W. Graves, Guardian for plaintiffs. Before Division One: Lisa White Hardwick, Presiding Judge, Edward R. Ardini, Jr. and Thomas N. Chapman, Judges

ORDER

Per Curiam

S.L. appeals the judgments terminating his parental rights to three children, C.J.L., S.L.L., and L.D.L. He contends the circuit court erred in terminating his parental rights for failure to rectify because the juvenile officer failed to establish that Children's Division ("Division") made diligent and repeated efforts to utilize all available services related to meeting his needs. Upon review of the briefs and the record, we find no error and affirm the judgments. We have provided the parties with a Memorandum explaining the reasons for our decision, because a published opinion would have no precedential value.

AFFIRMED. Rule 84.16(b).
